      <data key="d7">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR CHANGE RATE (ACH)</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">ACH is the quantitative flow-rate parameter associated with operation of the ventilation system, even though the passage emphasizes that design may be more important than flow rate alone. | The passage states that ventilation system design, when aligned with the hypothesized path principle, may be a more important factor than flow rate alone for contaminant transmission control.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.88</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
